Kristopher Hicks was on his way home from a night out in Bath with his girlfriend in 2010 . 
  He was in a taxi driven by Michael Young who mistakenly thought he was planning to 'do a runner' Mr Young decided to drive Mr Hicks back to the rank in a bid to teach him a lesson . 
  But when Mr Hicks objected he was driven for almost a mile at 20mph . 
  Mr Hicks jumped from the taxi and suffered devastating brain injuries . 
  His family took Mr Young to the High Court where a judge ruled he had unlawfully imprisoned Mr Hicks . 
  Mr Young was ordered to pay Mr Hicks compensation for the incident . 
 